**What is Endometriosis?**
- Tissue similar to uterine lining grows elsewhere
| Common locations: ovaries, fallopian tubes, bladder, bowel
| This tissue responds to hormones just like uterine lining
| Can cause pain, scarring, and infertility

**Common Symptoms:**
| Pelvic pain (especially during periods)
| Pain with intercourse
| Heavy or irregular bleeding
| Pain with bowel movements or urination
| Infertility

**Diagnosis:**
| Medical history and symptom review
| Physical exam
| Imaging (ultrasound, MRI)
| Laparoscopy (definitive diagnosis)

**Treatment Options:**
| Pain relievers (NSAIDs)
| Hormonal therapies (birth control pills, progestins)
| Surgery to remove implants
| Lifestyle changes

**Impact on Fertility:**
| Can make it harder to get pregnant
| Many women with endometriosis can still get pregnant
| Treatment may improve fertility

**Remember:** Endometriosis is common and treatable. If you have symptoms, talk to a healthcare provider.
